The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Calcutta: Australian Michael Hussey, on the strength of an outstanding series against Pakistan, has replaced India captain Mahendra Singh Dhoni at the top of the Reliance Mobile ICC Player Rankings for ODI batsmen.     
	Hussey had started the series trailing Dhoni by 21 points and now leads the Indian captain by three points after the list was updated Monday. It is the first time since January 2009 that Dhoni has slipped from the top spot. In the team rankings, Australia have opened up a 12-point gap with second-placed India, after winning three ratings points for the clean sweep.                  
	New Delhi: The Australian Cricketers Association Monday asked the IPL authorities to show common sense and share the security plans for the event with it so that it can advice players on their participation in the T20 league.      
	Squash meet  
	New Delhi: Ace Indian squash players Saurav Ghoshal and Dipika Pallikal will take part in the Case Swedish Open to be held in Linkping, Sweden from February 4-7.  
	Om gets bronze  
	Flagstaff (US): Indian shot putter Om Prakash Singh started his preparation for the Commonwealth Games with a bronze medal at the Mountain T Indoor meet here. The current Asian champion set a new indoor personal best of 19.37m.  
	McCarthy move  
	London: South Africa striker Benni McCarthy joined West Ham United from Premier League rivals Blackburn Rovers on Monday, five years after a planned move to the London club fell through.  
	New coach  
	Madrid: Villarreal have promoted Juan Carlos Garrido to first-team coach until the end of the season following the sacking of Ernesto Valverde, the La Liga club said on their website on Monday.  
	Benitez word  
	London: Liverpool manager Rafa Benitez reiterated his commitment to the Premier League club on Sunday after media reports in Italy linked him with a move to Juventus.  
	Big draw  
	Miami: The Uefa Champions League final has for the first time replaced the NFL Super Bowl as the most-watched annual sports event, according to a survey.                                                                                                                                                  
